  "prompt": "What exactly is Gusto?",
  "response": "Gusto is a cloud-based platform that provides an array of services primarily aimed at small and medium-sized businesses to help them manage their human resources, payroll, and benefits. Founded in 2011, Gusto simplifies and automates various HR processes including:\n\n1. **Payroll Management:** Automates the calculations, filings, and payments of payroll taxes. It also handles various payroll-related tasks such as direct deposits, W-2s, and year-end reporting.\n\n2. **Employee Benefits Administration:** Offers a range of benefits like health insurance, retirement plans, and commuter benefits. It streamlines the process of managing employee benefits by integrating them into the payroll process.\n\n3. **HR Tools:** Provides features for new employee onboarding, time tracking, employee self-service, and compliance management. These tools help businesses keep track of employee records, performance evaluations, and other HR-related activities.\n\n4. **Compliance and Legal Support:** Assists in ensuring compliance with various employment regulations and laws, which can include new hire reporting and maintaining necessary labor law posters.\n\nBy integrating payroll, benefits, and HR functions into one platform, Gusto aims to reduce the administrative workload on business owners and HR professionals, allowing them to focus more on strategic tasks and growth initiatives.",
